Data Viewer

    In order to make observations of your digital data, you need a tool to
    visualise and navigate your data in a manner that makes observations easier.
    The original MacSHAPA provided support for digital video, but with OpenSHAPA
    we are going much further. We are creating a plugin architecture that allows
    users to drop down different tracks of data Ð these tracks could come from
    any kind of source: video, sound, even output from various measuring
    equipment such as goniometers and gaitmats. The proposed interface for
    OpenSHAPA (see figure below) will allow users to quickly and easily
    synchronise your data so that it is all temporally aligned. This feature is
    under active specification and development, and we would appreciate your
    help Information on how you can contribute can be found
    {{{https://openshapa.org/fogbugz/default.php?W20}here.}}

