Reports

    While OpenSHAPA allows you to export your observations in a simple CSV file
    so that you can do statistical analysis in other applications. We are
    planning to add support for many reports that existed in the original
    MacSHAPA, we are always on the lookout for new ideas and suggestions on
    other reports we could include in OpenSHAPA Ð Information on how you can
    contribute can be found {{{https://openshapa.org/fogbugz/default.php?W20}here.}}

Extendable

    OpenSHAPA is embedded with a scripting engine based on the ruby language,
    enabling you to programatically manipulate your observations with scripts.
    This scripting language allows you to easily query, export and clean
    observations stored in the database.